CLUE: Port and largest city of Burma
OUTPUT: ['Founded in 1755 by King Alaungpaya, it was named "Yangon" which means "End of Strife." Over time, Yangon became an important trading center due to its strategic location near the mouth of the Yangtze River Delta and its accessibility via maritime routes.', "Historically, Yangon served as the capital when Burma was under British colonial rule before 1948; however, after independence, the government moved the capital to Naypyidaw in 2006 due to strategic planning for a new administrative center away from the country's ethnic divisions."]
